Save the date: The first Peterbilt of Council Bluffs Truck Show will be held on Saturday, May 5 at the dealership.
"There is no entry fee and trucks of all makes are welcomed to participate in this show and shine," said event coordinator Bruce Cash.
The truck show will be held on the large new concrete customer parking lot on the north side of the Council Bluffs dealership. Registration is scheduled from 8-11 a.m.
"This will be a participants-judged show and attendees will be able to vote on People’s Choice Awards. First, second and third place awards will be handed out for various truck classes," Cash said. The public is invited to attend, admission is free.
Other activities include food vendors, booths, door prizes and more. The Council Bluffs parts store will be open all day with Truck Show Specials! The CB Service Center will offer service specials till noon.
Truck Show participants are encouraged to preregister in advance. Contact Bruce Cash in the Peterbilt of Council Bluffs Parts Department at 712-328-7736 or toll-free 800-454-7383 or e-mail bcash@pbtruck.com. http://bit.ly/IcKXLQ﻿

Google Plans 2nd Data Center in Council Bluffs, Iowa
Google has announced to invest $300 million in building a new data center at Coucil Bluffs near Bunge and Wabash Avenue. It brings the total investment to western Iowa city to about $900 million. Construction will begin immediately on a 1,000 acre site south of Council Bluffs. Google's existing $600 million data center opened in 2009. The current facility supports Google Search, Gmail and Google Maps. It accommodates about 241,280 servers.﻿
